content.description: This route is super hard to decipher

Intricate moves up the arete start with decent side-pulls and bring you to a tough crux with difficult feet. Grab some slopers out left and throw an improbable heel hook to gain jugs to the finish. The guidebook suggests an optional TCU near the top. While the finish traverses and is a bit run out, a piece doesn't seem necessary.
content.location: Right of Power Hitter, finishing on the same anchor

content.description: Climb up finger cracks with good gear to a slight run-out. Venture into face climbing with one bolt before chain anchors.
content.location: Furthest left route at M &M Wall.

content.description: awesome awesome stemming!  crux comes at the 4th bolt if i remember right.  whats good?  all of it.  whats bad?  nothing i can think of.  its super techy..
content.location: to the right of Hang Overhang.  its a left facing dihedral with chalk all up and down it!

content.description: Fun route and a nice introduction to rattly fingers crack climbing for the first couple moves.
content.protection: Several finger sized cams (yellow, green aliens) into the last couple bolts of Sidesaddle, shares anchors
content.location: Just to the left of Ridin Sidesaddle

content.description: Climb the finger crack and face to top with one bolt along the way.
Start up chimney to first clip.  fingerlock to get out of chimney.  keep going.  This climb felt like a bolted crack climb.  Fingerlocks around blocks the whole way.
content.location: the far end of m&m wall.

content.description: Start with stem moves and hands in a crack past the first bolt.  An optional piece in the crack before the first bolt isn't a bad idea.  Head for the crescent and work your way up on some fun, strenuous layback moves.
content.protection: 4 bolts and an optional piece before the first bolt (0.5-0.75)
content.location: Toward the right end of the M&M wall, just right of Cold Cut Combo

content.description: Thought-provoking climb with an interesting dihedral stem/mantle crux that's just run-out enough to make you think about it.
content.location: Just right of Fifteen Minutes of Fame with an obvious "pod" about 2/3 of the way up.

content.description: Step up on large edges until above the second bolt, then size up the blank-looking arete.  There are tiny openings in the seam to your left, but those with even moderate-sized fingers will find them useless.  Hit the arete with everything you've got and inch your way up until you can hit the jug above.  Celebrate and romp up and left to the chains.
content.location: Far right end of the wall

content.description: great warm-up and possibly the only warm-up in this area.  good quality to boot!
content.location: to the right of Stemmin' Ms, climb up the pillar (left side) to access high first bolt.

content.description: reachy climbing to the second the bolt, good luck getting to the third, third to fourth is tough but it starts to ease up and finishes off fairly easy.  i've listed it as 11c because thats what both books say but i felt it was as hard or harder as Stemmin' Ms (12a to the right)

Start in an alcove with a pillar to your left.  Face climb and stem your way past two bolts.  It's unclear how much of the pillar on the left is "in" for this climb.  If it is, you can get a no-hands rest before firing for the third bolt.  The section up to the third bolt and then moving past it to the fourth is the crux, with some thin, balance-intensive moves.  Don't blow the third clipa rope-in-hand fall would deck.
content.protection: 4 bolts, with the third being a good ways up and left of the second
content.location: In a little alcove between The Pod and Ridin' Sidesaddle

content.description:
Fun climb starting to the right of the bolt line and then moving up and left.  Jugs will get you up past a couple of bolts, then some fancy footwork will help you get up and left, then around the nose.

The original line left of the new start looks spicy at 11d.

start off on awesome overhanging jugs (campus moves optional) to a double crack with stemming.  getting on top of this off to the right you'll have the option of going left for the 10c or straight up (slightly right) over the bulge for the 11a version. deepest thoughts?  i thought this was one of the best routes i did in the area.
content.protection: 4 or 5 bolts to chains.  i put pg-13 because if you fell (you wont) clipping the 2nd bolt you'd most likely deck.  but like i said you wont.
content.location: its considered to be on the right side of M&M.  and to the left of huge pillar that fell off of Power Hitter (you'll see it).  also look for campus style moves off the deck leading to two cracks within reach of each other! fun!
